Create EC2 instance

connect - ssh -i your-key.pem ec2-user@your-public-ip
sudo yum update -y
sudo yum install docker -y
sudo service docker start
sudo usermod -aG docker ec2-user

Now logout and reconnect:
exit
Reconnect again:
ssh -i your-key.pem ec2-user@your-public-ip
Check Docker:
docker --version
You should see version.

mkdir mywebserver
cd mywebserver

Step 4: Create simple HTML page
Create file:
nano index.html
Paste:
<html>
<head>
<title>My First Docker Web Server</title>
</head>
<body>
<h1>Hello from Docker on AWS EC2</h1>
</body>
</html>
Save:
CTRL + O
ENTER
CTRL + X

Step 5: Create Dockerfile
Now create Dockerfile:
nano Dockerfile
Paste:
FROM nginx:latest
COPY index.html /usr/share/nginx/html/index.html
Save again.

Step 6: Build Docker image
Run:
docker build -t myweb:v1 .

Step 7: Check image
docker images
You will see:
myweb v1

Step 8: Run container
docker run -d -p 80:80 myweb:v1

Step 9: Check running container
docker ps
You should see running container.
